{{Top|leg}}
The '''Ratitan whisperfly''' was a tiny insect from the [[Ratit system/Legends|Ratit system]] known for its low, insistent buzzing. As such, it was used as [[List of phrases and slang|slang]] for a rule or order one stubbornly stuck by.<ref name="SotP">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>

==History==
In [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Talon Karrde]] considered [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] to have figuratively put a Ratitan whisperfly into [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]]'s ear, when the latter constantly reminded Karrde of the former's orders that his presence wasn't to be made known while meeting onboard the ''[[Errant Venture/Legends|Errant Venture]]''.<ref name="SotP" />

